                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9068</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="45" xml:id="d224fn45">Handed to the British Ambassador by the Chief of
                        the Division of Far Eastern Affairs, July 20.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        type="received-date" when="1937-07-20">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Secretary of State expects to speak again tomorrow with the Japanese and the
                    Chinese Ambassadors and urge upon them the view of this Government that it is
                    most important that hostilities be avoided.</p>
            </div>
